unittitle.value: Guantanamo Bay Detention Camp Collection: Dorsey and Whitney, LLP Records

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: This collection documents the detention of six Bahraini men at the Guantanamo Bay Detention Camp and their legal representation by a group of attorneys from the firm of Dorsey & Whitney, LLP. Included are correspondence, a variety of legal documents, and press from online and print sources.

p.value: Researchers must consult with staff before accessing collection.

Published citations should take the following form: 
                <lb/>
                <lb/>Identification of item, date; Collection name; Collection number; box number; folder number; 
                <lb/>Tamiment Library/Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives 
                <lb/>Elmer Holmes Bobst Library 
                <lb/>70 Washington Square South 
                <lb/>New York, NY 10012, New York University Libraries.

By August 2007 all six of the men had been released -- Adel Kamil Abdulla Haji (Al Wadi), Salman Bin Ibrahim Bin Mohammed Bin Ali Al Khalifa, and Abdullah Majed Sayyah Hasan Al Noaimi, in November 2005; Salah Abdul Rasul Ali Al Bloushi in October 2006; Jum'ah Mohammed Abdul Latif Al Dossari in July 2007; and Isa Ali Abdulla Al Murbati in August 2007.

Several lengthy essays from publications in the U.S. and the U.K. (e.g. 
                <emph render="italic">The New Yorker</emph>, 
                <emph render="italic">American Lawyer</emph>, 
                <emph render="italic">The New York Review of Books</emph>, 
                <emph render="italic">Harper's Magazine</emph> and 
                <emph render="italic">The Telegraph</emph>) provide more detail and opinion. Press coverage from such a variety of perspectives helps give a more comprehensive overview of the experiences of the six Bahraini detainees in particular and the Guantanamo Detention Camp issues in general.
